The paper deals with cross-language information retrieval and machine translation, which are core topics in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed method involves identifying mappings between attributes from infoboxes, which are structured data, and thus, falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). The approach is completely automated and scalable, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and possibly deep learning (cs.LG).
